ds":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":true,"disclosed_at":"2023-12-14T18:55:58.977Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2023-12-14T12:12:52.725Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2023-12-14T18:55:58.829Z","comments_closed?":true,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hi, team!\n\n## Summary:\nBy changing the steamID cookie on confirm 2fa code request, I am able to block the login of an account with 2fa for 5 minutes (300 seconds).\nSo I am able to block users with 2fa from login into their accounts by just knowing the SteamID.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n\n  1. Login into your account with 2fa. \n1. Get the request to confirm the 2fa code.\n\n{F1282394}\n\n\n```http\nPOST /login/confirm HTTP/1.1\nHost: cs.money\nContent-Length: 28\nConnection: close\nCookie: steamid=\u003cvictim_steam_id\u003e;\n\n{\"token\":\"foo\",\"code\":\"foo\"}\n```\n\n2. Change the cookie steamid to the victim one.\n3. Repeat the request 4 times (4 wrong codes).\n\n-------\n\n█████\n\n## Impact\n\nI hacker could block everyone with 2fa from login into cs.money.","bounty_amount":"300.0","formatted_bounty":"$300","weakness":{"id":97,"name":"Reliance on Cookies without Validation and Integrity Checking in a Security Decision"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":1282394,"file_name":"Screenshot_71.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/ndwnrtzl9zm0i4jizlymgln7frwq?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22Screenshot_71.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27Screenshot_71.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQWTIKESA4%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T072830Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECcaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJHMEUCIBdFw7u95MmU3R%2FZBtltwuvKy7D3FduQTxg%2BYOi%2BDG3hAiEApXgrXJvWyPsMBMvP80EMipHB2sHe2